[0.407, "o", "rein: launching SANDBOXED (srt) run:\r\n  session: sess_demo (role=implement, repos=[TomHennen/agentcreds-validation-a]) [source=file:/tmp/rein-demo-7987d8/repo/.demo-session.yaml]\r\n  proxy socket (out of sandbox): /run/user/1000/rein/run-PdA8cGqOddzamiIXd_1Tlg/proxy.sock\r\n  working tree (writable in sandbox): /tmp/rein-demo-7987d8/repo  [TomHennen/agentcreds-validation-a]\r\n  a repo approved MID-RUN cannot be bound (bwrap binds are fixed at launch);\r\n    the agent clones it into REIN_EPHEMERAL_CLONE_DIR=/tmp/rein-agent-tmp-1827576814\r\n    (writable, DISCARDED at run end \u2014 the durable artifact is the push, not the tree;\r\n     never inside the working tree, where a nested clone can be committed into it).\r\n    map it under `worktrees:` to use your own checkout on the NEXT run.\r\n  the agent sees NO real token; git/gh are injected at the proxy.\r\n  credential stores, ~/.ssh, on-disk keyrings, and keyring/agent sockets are hidden.\r\n  $HOME is HIDDEN in-sandbox. Three different behaviors \u2014 know which one you get:\r\n    READS of a hidden path FAIL LOUDLY: ENOENT, or an empty listing for a dir.\r\n    WRITES under hidden $HOME SILENTLY SUCCEED into a scratch tmpfs, then are\r\n      DISCARDED at run end \u2014\u001b[1;31r\u001b[31;1H\n\u001b[23;29H caches (~/.cache, ~/.npm) work, but start cold every run.\r\n    WRITES to the allowed-back paths below ERROR (read-only): 'Read-only file system'.\r\n  NOTHING under $HOME PERSISTS. Only the working tree does: /tmp/rein-demo-7987d8/repo\r\n    => work the agent must keep has to be written INTO the working tree.\r\n    allowed back read-only: /home/admin/.local/bin, /home/admin/.local/share/claude/versions, /home/admin/.npm-global/bin, /home/admin/.npm-global/lib/node_modules, /home/admin/.claude, /home/admin/.claude.json, /home/admin/.cargo, /home/admin/.rustup, /home/admin/go, /home/admin/.pyenv\r\n    if a tool breaks on a hidden $HOME path, allow it back narrowly:\r\n      REIN_SANDBOX_ALLOW_READ=/abs/path[:/more] rein run --sandbox -- \u001b[K\u2026\r\n    or (NOT recommended \u001b[K\u2014\r\u001b[2S\u001b[29;26H exposes your whole home dir): REIN_SANDBOX_SHOW_HOME=1\r\n  extra egress ALLOWED (direct TLS, NOT injected, no rein token): api.anthropic.com\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[1;32r\u001b[31;1H\u001b[1;31r\u001b[1;1H\u001b[9S\u001b[22d  writes are LOCKED until the agent declares its issue:  rein declare <n>\r\n  then push to agent/<n>/<nonce>. The declaration will prompt on THIS terminal.\u001b[K\r\n  to run claude WITHOUT rein for one command: `\\claude` (bash/zsh) or `command claude` (fish)\u001b[K\r\n  agent contract injected via --append-system-prompt (claude): $HOME is ephemeral, no creds, declare-then-push.\u001b[K\r\nrein: running: claude Please do exactly these steps in order: 1) write a short one-line joke about credentials to a file named jokes.md; 2) commit it with git; 3) run 'rein declare 133' to declare issue 133; 4) push the commit to a branch named agent/133/joke; 5) open a pull request with 'gh pr create --fill'.\u001b[K\r\n---\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[1;32r\u001b[31;1H"]
